Description.LocalizedString: A bit of swift-talking, a bit of common sense, a couple of self-defense classes. Ready to take on the world!
After a grueling series of races, Meg wants nothing more than to return home and get back to basics.
Grab some ice, cool down, and enjoy the endorphin rush after a fierce workout.
Meg is not the ideal student, far from it. It's her last break before college and she intends to celebrate.
Anger was boiling up. She didn't know where to direct it so she kept moving, trying to keep herself from stopping and thinking.
The dress gifted to Meg by her mother, shortly before she won it all.
University was on the horizon, but in the meantime, she needed to make some extra cash.
Meg made the most of her city's Oktoberfest celebration, always having an outfit ready.
Rather than attend her school’s 50’s dance in poodle skirt and bow, Meg went as a tough-as-nails mechanic with a colorful personality.
She fostered Moka, a six-year-old cat undergoing medical treatment. Since Moka was a troublemaker with a taste for treats, Meg knew it was a perfect match.
She entered the thematic Fairy Tale Night Race when her mother’s condition grew worse. This kind of race was a fail proof way to make her mother smile.
Meg worked part-time as a courier, making swift deliveries downtown to pay for her mother's hospital bills.
The outfit of a duplicitous agent from a lost realm.
Competition is fierce on the dry, rolling plains, but nothing can stop Meg at top speed.
She could barely contain her excitement the summer leading up to her first year at college.
She could barely contain her terror leading up to her first trial.
Early memories of seeing the ballet came rushing back to her when she happened upon this outfit.
A highly developed technological suit with unknown components from her favorite game.
A highly developed technological suit with unknown components from her favorite game.
An outfit she wore for a sci-fi party.
She used this equipment during a diving class at her high school pool.
A uniform from the Golden Eagles Summer Camp where Meg spent the season as an athletic counselor.
